STONE PILE

You are given a pile of N stones. Each stone has an integer written on it. The stones are arranged in a stack, where the first element is at the top.

Two players, Aman and Akshat, take turns performing moves.

There are two types of moves:

Remove the top stone and place it at the bottom
Remove the top stone and discard it

RULES

Aman’s turn
Perform move 1 once
Then perform move 2 once

Akshat’s turn
Perform move 1 twice
Then perform move 2 once

Players take turns alternately, starting with Aman.

The process continues until only one stone remains.

TASK

Determine

Who performs the last move
Print 1 for Aman
Print 0 for Akshat
The value written on the last remaining stone

INPUT FORMAT

The first line contains an integer T
T is the number of test cases

For each test case
The first line contains an integer N
The second line contains N space-separated integers A1 A2 ... AN

OUTPUT FORMAT

For each test case, print two space-separated integers
Player who performed the last move and the remaining stone value

CONSTRAINTS

1 ≤ T ≤ 100
2 ≤ N ≤ 100000
-1000000000 ≤ Ai ≤ 1000000000
Sum of N over all test cases ≤ 1000000

SAMPLE INPUT

3
3
-5 0 5
4
-1 -3 2 4
6
-100000 0 0 100000 -1000000 1000000

SAMPLE OUTPUT

0 -5
1 2
1 0

EXPLANATION

Players alternately rotate and remove stones based on rules.
The process continues until only one stone remains.
Output shows the last player and the remaining stone value.
============================
import java.util.*;
public class Main{
    public static void main (String[] args) {
        Scanner sc=new Scanner(System.in);
        int t=sc.nextInt();
        while(t-->0){
            int n=sc.nextInt();
            Queue<Integer> q=new LinkeddList<>();
            for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
                q.add(sc.nextInt());
            }
            boolean aman=true;
            int player=-1;
            while(q.size()>1){
                if(aman){
                    q.add(q.poll());
                    q.poll();
                    player=1;
                } else{
                    q.add(q.poll());
                    q.add(q.poll());
                    q.poll();
                    player=0;
                }
                amam=!aman;
            }System.out.println(player+" "+q.peek());
        }
    }
}

